  "story_variants": {
    "en": "## Your Personal Email Assistant\n\nImagine sending 50 personalized birthday emails in under 5 seconds. Or automatically emailing a daily report to your team. Python makes this effortless.\n\n### What You'll Learn\n- Using Python's built-in `smtplib` module\n- Composing emails with `email.mime`\n- String formatting for personalization\n- Looping through a contact list\n\n### How Email Works (Simplified)\n1. **Connect** to an SMTP server (Gmail, Outlook, etc.)\n2. **Authenticate** with your credentials\n3. **Compose** the email (subject, body, recipient)\n4. **Send** and disconnect\n\n> **Safety tip:** Use App Passwords (not your real password) and environment variables to keep credentials secure!"
  },
